Image by Tobias Coetsee: Dan PatlanskyIn 2019, he also won the Sama Award for Best Rock Album for Perfection Kills.Shelter of Bones was recorded over a three-year period from 2019 to 2021. “The pandemic allowed me to take my time, and really think about how I want the songs to come across,” reflects Patlansky.“In many ways, I tried to keep the sound from past albums that I’ve become known for in my arrangements and songwriting, but definitely took some different turns along the way.”I’ve always seen a record as a time capsule of where an artist is in a particular time of their lives.” For Patlansky, Shelter of Bones covers a three-year period of many ups and downs, and, as a result, the South African guitarist believes the process has been a very interesting journey,” he said.I caught up with Dan prior to his departure….bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What is your job description?Creator of ear candy..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What does music mean to you?Everything.bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} My music is about…Expressing through the song..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What is your motto?One step at a time..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Fame is about…The world subscribing to your soul..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Retirement will happen when…I can afford to. .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} I don't do…Shopping malls and hookers..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} I would love to co-write with… Chris Stapleton.bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Where do you go for inspiration to create?Other artists.bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What is the most enjoyable aspect of your work?Playing to live crowds.bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{t